+Question:
+
+For mission `exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit`, step `step-004`, identify
+the strongest local repository materials for testing the three surviving
+Step-3 candidates on explicit normalized exact packets and parameter families:
+`Template-Defect Near-Closure`,
+`Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`,
+and
+`Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`.
+
+Return concrete findings, not just file paths, on these exact questions:
+
+1. Which locally grounded packet choices or parameterized packet families are
+   the best Step-4 anti-circuit tests on the frozen one-bridge role-labeled
+   helical packet object with mandatory conjugate completion?
+2. Which locally grounded packet choices or parameterized packet families are
+   the best honest pro-circuit tests on that same frozen packet object?
+3. What local material sharpens the required adverse cases:
+   `Beltrami cancellation`,
+   `mirror-mode completion`,
+   `nearly degenerate triads`,
+   and
+   `tiny trigger modes`,
+   and what concrete exact-ledger effects should each case be expected to
