+## Pro-Family 2 - `F_SL(rho)`
+
+### Exact Interaction Data
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Freeze `0 < rho <= 1/12`.
+- `[INFERRED]` The normalized desired-channel forcing ledger is:
+
+  ```text
+  int_I |Q_clk|   = 1/4,
+  int_I |Q_seed|  = rho,
+  int_I |Q_amp|   = 1/4 - rho,
+  int_I |Q_rot^D| = 1/4,
+  int_I |Q_rot^A| = 1/8,
+  int_I |Q_next|  = 1/8.
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The normalized spectator ledger is:
+
+  ```text
+  int_I D_mirror     = rho,
+  int_I D_companion  = rho,
+  int_I D_feedback   = rho,
+  int_I D_cross      = rho^2.
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` So the leakage totals are
+
+  ```text
+  L_mirror    = rho,
+  L_companion = rho,
+  L_feedback  = rho,
+  L_cross     = rho^2,
+  L_tot       = 3 rho + rho^2.
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Event-time information on the fixed window:
+
+  ```text
+  t_clk  = 1/5,
+  t_trig = 2/5,
+  t_rot  = 4/5,
+  t_next = 1 - O(rho)  or drifts beyond 1 as rho -> 0.
+  ```
+
+  The family keeps leakage tiny on the fixed window, but the local record does
+  not provide a closed exact amplitude system that pins `t_next` uniformly
+  inside `I` across the whole scale-separated family.
+
+### Candidate Outcomes On `F_SL(rho)`
+
+| Candidate | Outcome | Named reason |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| `Template-Defect Near-Closure` | `passes` | desired channels remain within the frozen template tolerances while spectator defect stays `O(rho)` |
+| `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` | `passes` | all classwise leakage ratios are below budget and the off-template load is dynamically negligible on `I` |
+| `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` | `remains ambiguous` | scale separation keeps leakage small but the exact `t_next` trace is not fixed uniformly on the current local record |
+
+### Diagnostic Vectors On `F_SL(rho)`
+
+- `[INFERRED]`
+
