+        4/5,
+        1 - O(rho) or > 1,
+        |C|_pretrigger^max < theta_C,
+        rotor_margin = 1/2,
+        max_{t in [0, 1]} D_off / D_on = 3 rho + rho^2
+      )
+  ```
+
+## Combined Exact-Packet Comparison
+
+### Obstruction-Facing Evidence
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` `F_BM` and `F_DT(delta, eta)` both fail the three candidate
+  sheets, but for different reasons:
+  `F_BM` is vacuous-static and is filtered out by `A_live`,
+  while `F_DT` is a live failure family with leakage overload and no trigger
+  activation.
+- `[INFERRED]` The cleanest obstruction signal still belongs to
+  `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`, because `F_DT` violates the classwise
+  budgets directly on the normalized exact ledger.
+
+### Construction-Facing Evidence
+
+- `[INFERRED]` `F_SS(mu)` is the clearest friendly family:
+  all three candidates pass on one fixed sign-coherent sparse-triad packet
+  family.
+- `[INFERRED]` `F_SL(rho)` shows the friendly picture is not purely cosmetic:
+  leakage can stay nonzero but dynamically negligible on the same frozen
+  window, and the template screen still passes.
+- `[INFERRED]` The only remaining instability on the friendly side is the
+  itinerary's dependence on a fully explicit event-time trace across the whole
+  scale-separated family.
+
+## Candidate Comparison Table
+
+| Candidate | Step-4 classification | Short reason | Negative drift |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| `Template-Defect Near-Closure` | `survives` | it fails both anti-circuit families but passes both pro-circuit families on one frozen role-template ledger | none earned |
+| `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` | `survives` | it cleanly separates live anti-circuit leakage overload from both friendly low-leakage families and is the sharpest exact obstruction-facing gate | none earned |
+| `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` | `remains ambiguous` | it passes the engineered-sign sparse family but the scale-separated family still lacks a uniformly fixed exact `t_next` trace on the local record | drifts toward `not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question` unless repaired |
+
+## Step-5 Readiness Verdict
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Chain Step 5 is now well posed.
+- `[INFERRED]` The anti/pro dossier is balanced:
+  two candidates survive the exact-packet screen,
+  and the third has one sharply named ambiguity rather than a vague failure.
+- `[INFERRED]` The one honest Step-5 repair pass may do exactly this:
+  - `Template-Defect Near-Closure`:
+    tighten `lambda_tmpl` and `lambda_spec` using only the anti/pro margins
+    already recorded here.
+  - `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`:
+    tighten `Lambda_tot` and the class budgets using only the recorded
+    anti/pro gap; no repartitioning is allowed.
+  - `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`:
+    either split into
+    `pre-trigger delay filter`
+    and
+    `next-stage transfer-start filter`,
+    or discard it if the scale-separated event-time ambiguity cannot be removed
+    without changing the window or the threshold language.
+- `[VERIFIED]` No Step-4 kill condition fired, because at least two candidates
+  are evaluable on explicit normalized exact families without hidden global
