+## Pro-Family 1 - `F_SS(mu)`
+
+### Exact Interaction Data
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Freeze `0 < mu <= 1/12`.
+- `[INFERRED]` The normalized desired-channel forcing ledger is:
+
+  ```text
+  int_I |Q_clk|   = 1/6,
+  int_I |Q_seed|  = mu,
+  int_I |Q_amp|   = 1/3 - mu,
+  int_I |Q_rot^D| = 1/4,
+  int_I |Q_rot^A| = 1/12,
+  int_I |Q_next|  = 1/6.
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The normalized spectator ledger is:
+
+  ```text
+  int_I D_mirror     = mu,
+  int_I D_companion  = mu,
+  int_I D_feedback   = mu / 2,
+  int_I D_cross      = mu / 2.
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` So the leakage totals are
+
+  ```text
+  L_mirror    = mu,
+  L_companion = mu,
+  L_feedback  = mu / 2,
+  L_cross     = mu / 2,
+  L_tot       = 3 mu.
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Event-time trace on the fixed window:
+
+  ```text
+  t_clk  = 1/6,
+  t_trig = 1/3,
+  t_rot  = 2/3,
+  t_next = 5/6.
+  ```
+
+  The family is engineered precisely so that the delayed clock, trigger,
+  rotor, and next-shell events all occur in order before `I` ends.
+
+### Candidate Outcomes On `F_SS(mu)`
+
+| Candidate | Outcome | Named reason |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| `Template-Defect Near-Closure` | `passes` | the friendly sign-coherent sparse geometry keeps the exact forcing close to the frozen Tao-role template with spectator defect `O(mu)` |
+| `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` | `passes` | all classwise leakage ratios are below the frozen budgets when `mu <= 1/12` |
+| `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` | `passes` | the family supplies one explicit ordered event tuple on the fixed window with spectator load `3 mu <= 1/4 < 1/3` |
+
+### Diagnostic Vectors On `F_SS(mu)`
+
+- `[INFERRED]`
+
+  ```text
+  v_tmpl(F_SS)
+    = (
+        Delta_tmpl = 2 mu,
+        Delta_spec = 2 mu,
+        1/6, mu, 1/3 - mu, 1/4, 1/12, 1/6,
+        mu, mu, mu / 2, mu / 2
+      )
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]`
+
+  ```text
+  v_leak(F_SS)
+    = (
+        3 mu,
+        mu,
+        mu,
+        mu / 2,
+        mu / 2,
+        1,
+        3 mu
+      )
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]`
+
+  ```text
+  v_itin(F_SS)
+    = (
+        1/6,
+        1/3,
+        2/3,
+        5/6,
+        |C|_pretrigger^max < theta_C,
+        rotor_margin = 3/4,
+        max_{t in [0, 5/6]} D_off / D_on = 3 mu
+      )
+  ```
+
+## Pro-Family 2 - `F_SL(rho)`
+
+### Exact Interaction Data
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Freeze `0 < rho <= 1/12`.
+- `[INFERRED]` The normalized desired-channel forcing ledger is:
+
+  ```text
+  int_I |Q_clk|   = 1/4,
+  int_I |Q_seed|  = rho,
+  int_I |Q_amp|   = 1/4 - rho,
+  int_I |Q_rot^D| = 1/4,
+  int_I |Q_rot^A| = 1/8,
+  int_I |Q_next|  = 1/8.
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The normalized spectator ledger is:
+
+  ```text
+  int_I D_mirror     = rho,
+  int_I D_companion  = rho,
+  int_I D_feedback   = rho,
+  int_I D_cross      = rho^2.
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` So the leakage totals are
+
+  ```text
+  L_mirror    = rho,
+  L_companion = rho,
+  L_feedback  = rho,
+  L_cross     = rho^2,
+  L_tot       = 3 rho + rho^2.
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Event-time information on the fixed window:
+
+  ```text
+  t_clk  = 1/5,
+  t_trig = 2/5,
+  t_rot  = 4/5,
+  t_next = 1 - O(rho)  or drifts beyond 1 as rho -> 0.
+  ```
+
+  The family keeps leakage tiny on the fixed window, but the local record does
+  not provide a closed exact amplitude system that pins `t_next` uniformly
+  inside `I` across the whole scale-separated family.
+
+### Candidate Outcomes On `F_SL(rho)`
+
+| Candidate | Outcome | Named reason |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| `Template-Defect Near-Closure` | `passes` | desired channels remain within the frozen template tolerances while spectator defect stays `O(rho)` |
+| `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` | `passes` | all classwise leakage ratios are below budget and the off-template load is dynamically negligible on `I` |
+| `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` | `remains ambiguous` | scale separation keeps leakage small but the exact `t_next` trace is not fixed uniformly on the current local record |
+
+### Diagnostic Vectors On `F_SL(rho)`
+
+- `[INFERRED]`
+
+  ```text
+  v_tmpl(F_SL)
+    = (
+        Delta_tmpl = 1/4,
+        Delta_spec = 3 rho + rho^2,
+        1/4, rho, 1/4 - rho, 1/4, 1/8, 1/8,
+        rho, rho, rho, rho^2
+      )
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]`
+
+  ```text
+  v_leak(F_SL)
+    = (
+        3 rho + rho^2,
+        rho,
+        rho,
+        rho,
+        rho^2,
+        1,
+        3 rho + rho^2
+      )
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]`
+
+  ```text
+  v_itin(F_SL)
+    = (
+        1/5,
+        2/5,
+        4/5,
+        1 - O(rho) or > 1,
+        |C|_pretrigger^max < theta_C,
+        rotor_margin = 1/2,
+        max_{t in [0, 1]} D_off / D_on = 3 rho + rho^2
+      )
+  ```
+
+## Combined Exact-Packet Comparison
+
+### Obstruction-Facing Evidence
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` `F_BM` and `F_DT(delta, eta)` both fail the three candidate
+  sheets, but for different reasons:
+  `F_BM` is vacuous-static and is filtered out by `A_live`,
+  while `F_DT` is a live failure family with leakage overload and no trigger
+  activation.
+- `[INFERRED]` The cleanest obstruction signal still belongs to
+  `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`, because `F_DT` violates the classwise
+  budgets directly on the normalized exact ledger.
+
+### Construction-Facing Evidence
+
+- `[INFERRED]` `F_SS(mu)` is the clearest friendly family:
+  all three candidates pass on one fixed sign-coherent sparse-triad packet
+  family.
+- `[INFERRED]` `F_SL(rho)` shows the friendly picture is not purely cosmetic:
+  leakage can stay nonzero but dynamically negligible on the same frozen
+  window, and the template screen still passes.
+- `[INFERRED]` The only remaining instability on the friendly side is the
+  itinerary's dependence on a fully explicit event-time trace across the whole
+  scale-separated family.
+
+## Candidate Comparison Table
+
+| Candidate | Step-4 classification | Short reason | Negative drift |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| `Template-Defect Near-Closure` | `survives` | it fails both anti-circuit families but passes both pro-circuit families on one frozen role-template ledger | none earned |
+| `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` | `survives` | it cleanly separates live anti-circuit leakage overload from both friendly low-leakage families and is the sharpest exact obstruction-facing gate | none earned |
+| `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` | `remains ambiguous` | it passes the engineered-sign sparse family but the scale-separated family still lacks a uniformly fixed exact `t_next` trace on the local record | drifts toward `not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question` unless repaired |
+
+## Step-5 Readiness Verdict
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Chain Step 5 is now well posed.
+- `[INFERRED]` The anti/pro dossier is balanced:
+  two candidates survive the exact-packet screen,
+  and the third has one sharply named ambiguity rather than a vague failure.
+- `[INFERRED]` The one honest Step-5 repair pass may do exactly this:
+  - `Template-Defect Near-Closure`:
+    tighten `lambda_tmpl` and `lambda_spec` using only the anti/pro margins
+    already recorded here.
+  - `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`:
+    tighten `Lambda_tot` and the class budgets using only the recorded
+    anti/pro gap; no repartitioning is allowed.
+  - `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`:
+    either split into
+    `pre-trigger delay filter`
+    and
+    `next-stage transfer-start filter`,
+    or discard it if the scale-separated event-time ambiguity cannot be removed
+    without changing the window or the threshold language.
+- `[VERIFIED]` No Step-4 kill condition fired, because at least two candidates
+  are evaluable on explicit normalized exact families without hidden global
+  regularity input or threshold shifts.
+
