+# Meta Note - Step 4 Exploration 001
+
+## What Worked
+
+- Freezing the anti-circuit and pro-circuit family menu before reading outcomes
+  stopped the step from sliding back into slogan-level comparisons.
+- Adding the `A_live` admissibility filter prevented exact static cancellation
+  packets from looking like positive near-circuit witnesses.
+
+## Reusable Lesson
+
+- A balanced exact-packet audit needs one explicit friendly family ledger and
+  one explicit hostile family ledger on the same normalization sheet.
+  Otherwise the later comparison is mostly a covert threshold rewrite.
+
+## Caution
+
+- Friendly sign engineering, sparse geometry, or scale separation can only be
+  tested honestly if the window, spectator partition, and packet sheet are
+  frozen first.
+  Without that order, the pro-circuit side turns into post hoc rescue.
+
