+
+- `[INFERRED]` `A_live`:
+  positive evaluation requires
+  `int_I D_on(t) dt > 0`.
+  This blocks vacuous passes on zero-activity Beltrami families.
+- `[VERIFIED]` `A_sheet`:
+  no family may change packet semantics, conjugate completion, spectator
+  partition, sign sheet after declaration, or time window.
+- `[VERIFIED]` `A_closure`:
+  all desired and classwise spectator channels must stay on the ledger.
+- `[INFERRED]` `A_trace`:
+  `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` may pass only if one explicit ordered event
+  tuple is present on the fixed window.
